Feeling the embrace of the open sea, I discovered the most profound therapy. My journey began in Cancún, 2021. The very thought of fish brushing against me while snorkeling filled me with dread. But here’s the thing about me - I am determined to face and conquer my fears.

In pursuit of this, Victor and I, guided by our friend Randall, plunged into basic ocean swimming lessons in Cabo San Lucas. Mastering the essentials, I moved on to an open water academy in the Palmilla region of San Jose Del Cabo, immersing myself for about a year.

In the Sea of Cortez, where the rich tapestry of marine life includes every conceivable whale and shark, my courage was repeatedly tested. Swimming beyond the bay required facing and overcoming those intense fears. Each stroke whispered Dory’s mantra, “just keep swimming,” even as my heart raced at the sight of every small rock.

Fast forward to this snapshot. Here I am, post my inaugural open water 2K charity swim, triumphant and not last 😜😜! This image mirrors another fear I'm learning to embrace – accepting my body. Yes, I am a big guy, but a healthy and hearty one too.

In sharing my vulnerability, my aim is to ignite that same courage in you. It’s your turn now. What fears are you ready to conquer? #FaceYourFears #justkeepswimming
